{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1772559813,"nonce":"gNVNRfDnKBXyIlFtNUFEcic3Ao0=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87vfNZpzwAAAAVo5as7"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772560254,"nonce":"GkaITJcLJNZqDQgZD8i5nUuRUzI=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87t-uHR","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/336#issuecomment-3992642001"},"message":"I think starting with official docs and key repos is a good idea. For changes between distros, they should be noted in the patterns file. Keep in mind the plan to support multiple distros. Conventions should target rolling, but allow exptions when working in a different distro and the new convention is not feasable.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772560698,"nonce":"mUNlHKCjuZLYzt8RM8AjNCm+mpY=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87t-36y","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/336#issuecomment-3992682162"},"message":"## Review\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** Yes — deliverables are clear: one ADR + one knowledge file update.\nSingle-PR sized. The \"open questions\" in the issue are design decisions to resolve\nduring planning, not scope creep.\n\n**Right repo?** Yes — this is workspace infrastructure (agent knowledge, ADR). It\naligns with ADR-0003: the conventions are generic ROS 2, not project-specific.\n\n**Dependencies**:\n- [#327](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/327) and\n  [#131](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/131) are sub-issues\n  that this umbrella addresses. Their enforcement work (pre-commit hooks, CI) remains\n  separate and can proceed independently after this ADR lands.\n- [#261](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/261) (multi-distro\n  support) is relevant — the owner's comment clarifies that conventions should target\n  Rolling but allow exceptions for other distros. This should be stated in the ADR.\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Enforcement over documentation | Watch | The ADR + knowledge file is the documentation layer. The issue correctly identifies enforcement (#265, #327 hooks) as separate follow-up work. The ADR should explicitly note that enforcement is expected per ADR-0004/0005. |\n| Capture decisions, not just implementations | OK | This is literally an ADR — exactly the right mechanism. |\n| A change includes its consequences | Watch | The knowledge file update is part of this PR. The consequences map entry for the new ADR and the `principles_review_guide.md` ADR table must also be updated in the same PR. |\n| Only what's needed | OK | Single umbrella ADR instead of per-convention ADRs — appropriately minimal. |\n| Workspace vs. project separation | OK | Generic ROS 2 conventions, not project-specific. |\n| Workspace improvements cascade to projects | OK | Project repos can reference the same knowledge file patterns. |\n\n### ADR Applicability\n\n| ADR | Triggered | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| 0001 — Adopt ADRs | Yes | This is a new ADR (0008). Follow the established format. |\n| 0003 — Project-agnostic workspace | Yes | Content must remain generic ROS 2. The issue correctly avoids project-specific references. |\n| 0004 — Enforcement hierarchy | Watch | The ADR should reference the enforcement hierarchy and note that the knowledge file alone is the \"instructions\" layer; hooks/CI are separate work items. |\n| 0005 — Layered enforcement | Watch | Same as above — the ADR is not enforcement, it's the decision that warrants enforcement. |\n| 0006 — Shared AGENTS.md | No | This doesn't change AGENTS.md. The knowledge file is a reference, not an instruction file. |\n\n### Consequences\n\nFrom the consequences map, creating a new ADR in `docs/decisions/` requires:\n- **Update `principles_review_guide.md`** — add ADR-0008 to the ADR applicability table\n- **Update `ros2_development_patterns.md`** — already planned as the main deliverable\n\n### Recommendations\n\n1. **Incorporate the owner's comment into the ADR decision**: conventions target Rolling,\n   with exceptions allowed when working in a different distro where a newer convention\n   isn't feasible. Reference [#261](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/261).\n\n2. **Explicitly reference ADR-0004/0005** in the ADR to clarify that the knowledge file\n   is the \"instructions\" layer, and enforcement (hooks, CI) is expected as separate work\n   per the established hierarchy.\n\n3. **Resolve the \"pin to Jazzy vs. Rolling\" question** in the ADR itself — the owner's\n   comment provides the answer (target Rolling, allow distro-specific exceptions).\n\n4. **Close [#327](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/327) and\n   [#131](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/131)** when this PR\n   merges (the guidance portions are addressed; enforcement work should get its own\n   issues if not already tracked).\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772564668,"nonce":"SLXrnEvEmIOet7qxWTa8vK667lM=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87vfNZpzwAAAAVpAjKH"},"status":2}]}